024Global energy consumption will grow by 1.8% in 2024, largely driven by strong demand in Asia. Despite still-high prices and unsolved supply chain disruptions, demand for fossil fuels will reach record levels, but demand for renewable energy will rise by 11%. Download report Finance outlook 2024High interest rates will determine the success or failure of almost every part of the financial services sector in 2024. Though painful for borrowers, banks will enjoy strong net interest margins next year. Download report Telecoms and technology outlook 2024Geopolitics will continue to affect technology in 2024. The tech battle between the US and China will persist in areas including artificial intelligence (AI), chips and quantum technologies. AI will receive increasing investment, but will encounter geopolitical and regulatory challenges. Download report Consumer goods and retail outlook 2024A slowdown in inflation will bolster retail volume growth by 6.7% in US dollar terms and 2% in volume terms in 2024. However, reduced savings and high food prices, worsened by the effects of climate change, will act as dampeners. Download report Healthcare outlook 2024A recovery in the global economy will cause a return to spending growth in the healthcare sector. However, it will remain vulnerable to headwinds, including limited resources, stricter regulations and continued strikes. Download report Download the free report Fill in the form below:  *First name:*Last name:*Company:*Business email:*Job Title:*Business phone:*Industry:Select...Academia & EducationAdvertising, Marketing & PRAgriculture, Forestry & FishingAutomotiveAviation, Aerospace & DefenceCharities, Foundations & NGO'sChemicalsConstruction, Engineering & InfrastructureConsulting / Professional ServicesEnergy, Utilities & RenewablesFinancial servicesFMCGGovernment & Public ServicesHealthcare & PharmaceuticalsIndustrial goods & ManufacturingIT & TechnologyMedia & EntertainmentMetals & MiningReal EstateRetail & Consumer