tomobile parts, is primarily driving the global auto parts manufacturing market. 4.  What has been the impact of COVID-19 on the global auto parts manufacturing market? The sudden outbreak of the COVID-19 pandemic had led to the implementation of stringent lockdown regulations across several nations, resulting in the temporary closure of numerous automotive manufacturing units, thereby negatively impacting the global market. 5.  What is the breakup of the global auto parts manufacturing market based on the component type? Based on the component type, the global auto parts manufacturing market can be segmented into battery, cooling system, underbody components, engine components, automotive filter, lighting components, electrical components, and others. Currently, engine components hold the majority of the total market share. 6.  What is the breakup of the global auto parts manufacturing market based on the sales channel? Based on the sales channel, the global auto parts manufacturing market has been divided into OEM and aftermarket, where OEM currently exhibits a clear dominance in the market. 7.  What is the breakup of the global auto parts manufacturing market based on vehicle type? Based on the vehicle type, the global auto parts manufacturing market can be categorized into passenger cars, light commercial vehicles, heavy commercial vehicles, and others. Among these, passenger cars account for the largest market share. 8.  What are the key regions in the global auto parts manufacturing market? On a regional level, the market has been classified into North America, Asia-Pacific, Europe, Latin America, and Middle East and Africa, where Asia-Pacific currently dominates the global market. 9.  Who are the key players/companies in the global auto parts manufacturing market? Some of the major players in the global auto parts manufacturing market include Aisin Corporation, Akebono Brake Industry Co. Ltd., Brembo S.p.A., Continental AG, DENSO Corporation, Faurecia SE, General Motors Company, Magna International Inc., Marelli Holdings Co. Ltd., Robert Bosch GmbH, Schaeffler AG, and Valeo. Need more help?             Speak to our experienced analysts for insights on the current market scenarios.                      Include additional segments and countries to customize the report as per your requirement.          Gain an unparalleled competitive advantage in your domain by understanding how to utilize the report and positively impacting your operations and revenue.                      For further assistance, please connect with our analysts.           Call  Email  Request Sample             Purchase options                                  Single User License                                                         $3899                         Five User License                                                         $4899                         Corporate User License                                                         $5899 Buy Now  Inquire Before Buying Speak to an Analyst      Request Brochure          Request Customization Benefits of Customization  Personalize this research         Triangulate with your data              Get data as per your format and definition      Gain a deeper dive into a specific application, geography, customer, or competitor         Any level of personalization      Get in Touch With Us         UNITED STATES              Phone: +1-631-791-1145              INDIA              Phone: +91-120-433-0800              UNITED KINGDOM              Phone: +44-753-713-2163              Email: sales@imarcgroup.com      Client Testimonials Previous IMARC was a good solution for the data points that we really needed and couldn't find elsewhere. The team was easy to work, quick to respond, and flexible to our customization requests.                     Read More                  IMARC made the whole process easy. Everyone I spoke with via email was polite, easy to deal with, kept their promises regarding delivery 