al markets. It further enables stakeholders to identify the key country-level markets within each region. Porter's five forces analysis assists stakeholders in assessing the impact of new entrants, competitive rivalry, supplier power, buyer power, and the threat of substitution. It helps stakeholders to analyze the level of competition within the auto parts manufacturing industry and its attractiveness. Competitive landscape allows stakeholders to understand their competitive environment and provides an insight into the current positions of key players in the market.         Key Questions Answered in This Report      1.  What was the size of the global auto parts manufacturing market in 2023? The global auto parts manufacturing market was valued at US$ 2,197.9 Billion in 2023. 2.  What is the expected growth rate of the global auto parts manufacturing market during 2024-2032? We expect the global auto parts manufacturing market to exhibit a CAGR of 2.39% during 2024-2032. 3.  What are the key factors driving the global auto parts manufacturing market? The rising adoption of Electric Vehicles (EVs), along with the growing demand for manufacturing effective and environmentally sustainable automobile parts, is primarily driving the global auto parts manufacturing market. 4.  What has been the impact of COVID-19 on the global auto parts manufacturing market? The sudden outbreak of the COVID-19 pandemic had led to the implementation of stringent lockdown regulations across several nations, resulting in the temporary closure of numerous automotive manufacturing units, thereby negatively impacting the global market. 5.  What is the breakup of the global auto parts manufacturing market based on the component type? Based on the component type, the global auto parts manufacturing market can be segmented into battery, cooling system, underbody components, engine components, automotive filter, lighting components, electrical components, and others. Currently, engine components hold the majority of the total market share. 6.  What is the breakup of the global auto parts manufacturing market based on the sales channel? Based on the sales channel, the global auto parts manufacturing market has been divided into OEM and aftermarket, where OEM currently exhibits a clear dominance in the market. 7.  What is the breakup of the global auto parts manufacturing market based on vehicle type? Based on the vehicle type, the global auto parts manufacturing market can be categorized into passenger cars, light commercial vehicles, heavy commercial vehicles, and others. Among these, passenger cars account for the largest market share. 8.  What are the key regions in the global auto parts manufacturing market? On a regional level, the market has been classified into North America, Asia-Pacific, Europe, Latin America, and Middle East and Africa, where Asia-Pacific currently dominates the global market. 9.  Who are the key players/companies in the global auto parts manufacturing market? Some of the major players in the global auto parts manufacturing market include Aisin Corporation, Akebono Brake Industry Co. Ltd., Brembo S.p.A., Continental AG, DENSO Corporation, Faurecia SE, General Motors Company, Magna International Inc., Marelli Holdings Co. Ltd., Robert Bosch GmbH, Schaeffler AG, and Valeo. Need more help?             Speak to our experienced analysts for insights on the current market scenarios.                      Include additional segments and countries to customize the report as per your requirement.          Gain an unparalleled competitive advantage in your domain by understanding how to utilize the report and positively impacting your operations and revenue.                      For further assistance, please connect with our analysts.           Call  Email  Request Sample             Purchase options                                  Single User License                                                         $3899                         Five